betterquesting:10.desc:8: You're probably going to want to get some wood to build a shelter.  Let's look for some basic building materials!
Put the craft in Minecraft!  Build yourself a crafting table!

If you picked the iron on the first quest, then you'll have a nice tool to start with but choose wisely! Go ahead and make yourself some tools to start.  These tools will have to do till you start making your way through Tinkers!
No not like that you fool!  Now that you've got yourself a fancy pickaxe it's time to get some stone! Stone is a useful material for the Nether as well as for building!

Alright, time to upgrade your crafting table.  Simply put the crafting table back in the crafting grid to get the much better Crafting Station.  This Crafting Station will hold your items in place instead of dropping them all over the place.  This is great for crafting a recipe over and over again!
Get you some windows instead of building a block of wood or stone so you can see outside.
Mine up some cobblestone and make yourself a furnace or multiple if you feel so inclined!
You'll definitely want this weapon.  This can become incredibly overpowered and is the best ranged weapon outside of guns...probably.  I haven't really used any guns before in Minecraft.

betterquesting:10.name:8: Set Your Spawn with a Bed!
betterquesting:10.desc:8: Quick!  Before you forget, make sure you gather some wool to make a bed to set your spawn. It's dangeroud out there!
You're gonna want to get your hands on some iron to start building your tools. Either using the vanilla iron pickaxe or start on Tinkers Construct to build your pickaxe!
Starting out basic with some chests.  Better make some storage so you don't clog your inventory.

You'll want to get some food to fend off your hunger.  Especially if you are using the Ore excavation or a large tinkers tool. Setting up a farm will be especially useful early on so you can build a good stock.  An efficient farm is 9x9 with a block of water in the middle.

Chests are a thing of the past!  With a Basic Storage Drawer, you can store 64 stacks of one item which is great for storing common items like cobblestone and wood.  Great way to immediately see where an item is instead of looking through every chest.
Can store more coal to burn as well as more material to cook.  A little faster than a vanilla furnace
Same as the Gold just made of copper!
Can store more coal to burn as well as more material to cook.  Even faster than the Iron Furnace!
Can store even more coal to burn as well as more material to cook.  The fastest furnace!
Same as the gold furnace just made of silver!
Requires no fuel to cook items however, each item will take 90 seconds to smelt.
Can smelt two sets of ore at the same time!

Make yourself a Drawer Controller in order to quickly empty your inventory and a compacting drawer.  The Drawer Controller automatically puts items stat are stored in the drawers.  Has a range of 12 in all directions.  The Compacting Drawer is great for storing metals like Iron.  It will automatically make 9 Iron Ingots into a block of iron or turn them into Iron Nuggets.
Use this to upgrade how much your drawers can hold.  Tiered upgrade system!
Use the key to lock your drawer.  When you lock your drawer, if you empty the drawer it will remember the item so your drawer doesn't get mixed up.
Even More Items!
Voids any excess items that you store in the drawer.
Make the basic tables for tinkering

Create the patterns needed for making your four basic tools the Tinker's way.  These tools will level up, gain modifiers that can be applied to the tools, and parts can be replaced with better materials!
Make a sword with tinkers!

Make some patterns for the smeltery.  This will be how you use the molten metals. Let's start with a basic sword! You'll probably want to make the other patterns for your tools if you have the gold to make them!

Time to gather lots of materials to build your smeltery.  A basic smeltery only needs to be 2x2 but can be expanded when you have more material.  Read more about it in the Tinker's book to learn about the sizes.  Or ask Matt.
A shuriken is a great weapon to start with for ranged!
These tools are excellent for doing mass amounts of mining if you don't want to vein mine!
Needed for the big equipment!
Time to find some diamond and Gold!  You may want to save these ores till you work on engineering where you can double your amount you get back!
You'll need some hemp to get going with industrial crafting!
You'll need a coke oven to make Creosote.  You'll also need to make an Engineer's hammer to create the multiblock!

betterquesting:10.name:8: I Want to Be an Engineer!
betterquesting:10.desc:8: To make steel you'll need a blast furnace.  You'll have to go to the Nether before you can make this. This can eventually be upgraded to be more efficient!
No Description
Explore the Nether and see what you can find.  Let's find the forrtress!
Find the portal to the end to face the Ender Dragon!
The cleaver is an excellent tool to get head....s of your enemies.  This is an excellent weapon for collecting Wither Skulls from those pesky Wither Skeletons.
Sorround a 2x2 pool of water with flowers and through a diamond in.  Get ready for the Twilight Zone
You'll need some Obsidian to build what will most likely be your first portal!
No Description
Your coke oven will generate creosote that you can then use on oak planks.  You'll need this to start generating power, so go ahead and make a stack of treated wood planks
Steel is a strong material and a vital material for Immersive Engineering.  Better learn how to make it!
Now that you've made some treated wood you can start generating power.  Make a water wheel and a windmill to build some power.  You'll see why soon.
You'll need a dynamo to retrieve power from your watermill and windmill.  You'll have to make a few things in order to craft this and one of the materials you will need is copper.
If you put the windmill sails on your windmill the windmill will generate power more efficiently.
You'll need this to make things like drill, the rail gun, the chemical thrower, and you know all the fun stuff!
You'll need to make some wires and connectors in order to connect your power to your machines.

This will probably be one of the first machines you want to make.  This will save you on copper when you are making copper plates and copper wires. Click the piston with the Engineer's Hammer to form the machine.  You get to choose one of the plates as a reward but you will have to make the other one.  This machine can be automated!

betterquesting:10.name:8: Bring Us the Girl, and Wipe Away the Debt!
betterquesting:10.desc:8:
A sky hook will let you swing around your base on the wires. 







Booker is Comstock
This furnace will generate steel faster and can be automated.  If you make the preheaters, you can make this machine even faster!
This Thermoelectric generator will create power with hot and cold materials directly next to them.
The Crusher will take any ore thrown into the top and turn it into two dust.  This is a really effective way to double your ore production!
The Squeezer is used for part of the production for Biodiesel which you will need to power the Diesel Generator if you want the max amount of power.  Get ready to burn through some more steel!
Defeat the Naga
You will also need the Fermenter in order to create Biodiesel.  Yay more steel!
And the moment you've been waiting for!  Time to make the Diesel Generator. This will be necessary for powering the larger machines!
Next up, the Refinery! You will need this in order to finally craft the Biodiesel!
Defeat the Licht King!
Backpacks can be crafted to give you additional space while you are travelling the world.  This can be made up to the diamond tier and they have room for upgrades!
Even more space!
MORE SPACE!!!!
SO MUCH SPACE FOR ACTIVITIES!!!!!
Your backpack can be upgraded but there's really not much use for them besides the one that makes it so it won't despawn.  Unless you want to protect your stuff from Joshua....

Creating a sword will most likely be your first attempt into fighting back.  You'll find which weapons you like to use more as you play. If you jump and swing as you are coming down you can get a critical strike on your enemies.  This is especially useful for fighting enemies like the Creeper!

The myth of the zombie seems like a tail as old as time.  Naturally, Minecraft brought the Zombie in as one of the enemies that you will most likely face first.  Defeat 50 Zombies over your time as an adventurer!
NYAHHH! Skeletons will fire from what seems like out of nowhere!  You may want to invest in a shield in order to defend yourself from their arrows!

What started out as a bug has now became a face of the franchise!  THe creeper will explode and make big holes.  Creeper explosions can be blocked from damaging you by using your shield.  I recommend that you sprint at the creeper to knock them back while fighting them.
Hehehe.  Witches will throw potions at you to weaken you and can stay alive with their own health potions.  They're not super common so you may find this trophy hard to get!

Endermen are tough enemies that can teleport all around.  They pickup blocks which can mess up your bases' astetic (questioning my spelling on that one).  A cheaty way to fight them is to stand under something that is three bricks high and swipe at the Enderman.  You'll have to fight a lot of Endermen in order to get to the end!

The Wither Skeletons are a dangerous mob.  They spawn in low level darkness and you'll need them if you want to fight The Wither.  Be careful!  When Wither Skeletons hit you, you will slowly lose health and can die from the Wither effect!
You'll need to fight the Blazes in order to get blaze rods to make potions.  This can be tricky as they seem to activate whenever your within a small radius of their spawn.

Spiders.  These devilish monsters seem to be everywhere and must be exterminated at all costs.  Everything is a weapon.  Light them on fire, drown them in water, shoot them with your arrow, hit them with your sword.  WHATEVER IT TAKES!
Kill some cows if your looking for meat. Or! If you want to have a renewable group of cows, fence two cows together and breed them and THEN slaughter and thin the herd!
Sheep provide you wool and Mutton

betterquesting:10.name:8: I Smell Bacon, I Smell Pork!
betterquesting:10.desc:8: Run Piggy Piggy I've got my fork!
Maybe slay some chickens over here.  Better signal.

Be careful with this fight.  When the Wither spawns it will be invulnerable for a few short moments and then there will be an explosion.  The first phase you will be able to fight it using ranged weapons.  In the second phase it will be invulnerable to range weapons so you'll need to attack with your swords.  This thing will destroy, EVERYTHING, around it.  Do NOT summon this in your base! When you get hit by the Wither, you will have the Withering effect so watch your health!

The Dragon can be a tough fight but not with friends.  First, destroy the crystals on the pillars around the dragon and then you will be able to damage the Ender dragon.  Be careful that you don't look the endermen in the eyes that are near you!

Deep in the ocean biome, you will find the layer of the Guardians.  There are rewards for you to obtain but you'll need to be able to breathe underwater, fight under water, and mine underwater.  These abilities can be gained through brewing potions.  Good luck on this quest!
Find the maze located in the dark forest to hunt down the Minotaur.  This will give you Meef Stroganoff which you will need in order to enter the Firey Swamp
Put the Phantom Knight's soul to rest in order to start gaining access to the Ur-Ghast Tower!
When you cut off one head, two more grow in its place.  Seriously, make sure your paying attention to where your hitting or you'll be dealing with lots of head!  And not the good kind!
Travel to the icey lands of the Twilight Forest to fight Elsa, I mean the Snow Queen!

In the center of the Dark Forest is a tower.  You will find it challenging to fight your way to the top where you will face the Ur-Ghast in a Ghostbusters like fight to the death where you use it's children as bait!  Easy peasy for a team of three!
Find the Quest Ram in the Twilight Forest and feed it one of each color of wool (16 in total)  to receive treasure
Find and defeat the boss of the Bronze Dungeon
Bring a saddle and ride your trusty steed! Which happens to be part Cow.  This will be great for jump from isle to isle while in the Aether!
Find and fight the boss of the Silver Dungeon!
Craft a portal to the Aether!
Craft the Thaumnomicon using salis mundis on a bookshelf

If you want to get around the world in style, craft a glider for yourself!  In combination with a slime sling from Tinkers this is a quick way to explore the world!  You get slime boots as a reward which I highly recommend you wear in case you "accidentally" let go of your hang glider.
The Builder's Wand is an awesome tool for building quickly.  You won't be able to make the unbreakable one till you have retrieved a nether star.
Constructing a beacon will empower you with additional abilities.  You will need a nether star to craft this sucker!

betterquesting:10.name:8: Ender Dragon Round 2: Electric Boogaloo: This Time It's Serious
betterquesting:10.desc:8: Construct four End Crystals to fight the End Dragon again!
Beginning in this crazy world
A better way to store and cook up your stuff!
Leveling up with Tools!
Let's get industrial up in here!
Quests for all of the dimensions!
Your quest will involve many battles!
